  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (coverage gap adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence covers the nominal 3–6 L/min flow range at 3000–4500 RPM; edge cases are noted as studied separately.",
